The paper discusses interference management techniques in wireless networks, which is a common topic in the Information Theory (cs.IT) sub-category. The use of convex relaxation and optimization algorithms also suggests that the paper could belong to the Numerical Analysis (cs.NA) sub-category. The focus on MIMO (multiple-input multiple-output) systems and interference channels suggests that the paper could also belong to the Networking and Internet Architecture (cs.NI) and Signal Processing (cs.SI) sub-categories. The use of simulation results and performance evaluation suggests that the paper could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG) sub-category.
